zymase definition: an enzyme or enzyme complex of yeast that promotes fermentation of sugar.
Zymase is an enzyme complex that catalyzes the fermentation of sugar into ethanol and carbon dioxide.

wiki.text:
'Zymase' is an enzyme complex that catalyzes the fermentation of sugar into
ethanol and carbon dioxide. It occurs naturally in yeasts. Zymase activity
varies among yeast strains.<ref></ref>

Zymase is also the brand name of the drug pancrelipase.
